TY  - JOUR
T1  - Managerial Perceptions of Employee Commitment to the Organization
AU  - Shore, Lynn Mcfarlane
AU  - Barksdale, Kevin
AU  - Shore, Ted H.
Y1  - 1995/12/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256845
DO  - 10.5465/256845
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1593
EP  - 1615
VL  - 38
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A model incorporating antecedents and outcomes of measures of manager-rated employee affective and continuance commitment was tested with 231 managers and 339 subordinates. Organizational citizenship behavior predicted manager-rated affective commitment, whereas side bets (age, tenure, and education) predicted manager-rated continuance commitment. Further, affective commitment was positively and continuance commitment negatively related to a variety of outcomes, including managerial potential and promotability. Implications are discussed.
AB  - A model incorporating antecedents and outcomes of measures of manager-rated employee affective and continuance commitment was tested with 231 managers and 339 subordinates. Organizational citizenship behavior predicted manager-rated affective commitment, whereas side bets (age, tenure, and education) predicted manager-rated continuance commitment. Further, affective commitment was positively and continuance commitment negatively related to a variety of outcomes, including managerial potential and promotability. Implications are discussed.
